e,"autumn":true,"winter":true},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1512453979798-5ea266f8880c?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Dubai  \u00b7  Abu Dhabi  \u00b7  Al Ain  \u00b7  The Empty Quarter","n":""},{"i":"orig-caribbean","t":"Caribbean","c":"Beach","r":"Caribbean","s":"Year-Round","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":true,"autumn":true,"winter":true},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1548574505-5e239809ee19?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"St. Barths  \u00b7  Turks & Caicos  \u00b7  Antigua  \u00b7  St. Lucia  \u00b7  Anguilla","n":""},{"i":"orig-newzealand","t":"New Zealand","c":"Adventure","r":"South Pacific","s":"Year-Round","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":true,"autumn":true,"winter":true},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1469521669194-babb45599def?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Queenstown  \u00b7  Milford Sound  \u00b7  Bay of Islands  \u00b7  Rotorua","n":""},{"i":"orig-oman","t":"Oman","c":"Adventure","r":"Arabian Peninsula","s":"Year-Round","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":true,"autumn":true,"winter":true},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1547036967-23d11aacaee0?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Muscat  \u00b7  Wahiba Sands  \u00b7  Wadi Shab  \u00b7  Nizwa  \u00b7  Musandam","n":""},{"i":"orig-madagascar","t":"Madagascar","c":"Adventure","r":"Indian Ocean","s":"Year-Round","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":true,"autumn":true,"winter":true},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1580181820272-6d72c9166f4b?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Avenue of the Baobabs  \u00b7  Andasibe  \u00b7  Isalo  \u00b7  Nosy Be  \u00b7  Tsingy","n":""},{"i":"orig-ethiopia","t":"Ethiopia","c":"Adventure","r":"East Africa","s":"Year-Round","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":true,"autumn":true,"winter":true},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1523805009345-7448845a9e53?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Addis Ababa  \u00b7  Lalibela  \u00b7  Simien Mountains  \u00b7  Omo Valley  \u00b7  Danakil","n":""},{"i":"tf-seasonal__festival-01","t":"German Christmas Markets","c":"Seasonal & Festival","r":"Central Europe","s":"November \u2013 December","ss":{"spring":false,"summer":false,"autumn":false,"winter":true},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1512389142860-9c449e58a543?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Nuremberg  \u00b7  Rothenburg  \u00b7  Cologne  \u00b7  Strasbourg  \u00b7  Dresden","n":"Nuremberg's Christkindlesmarkt is the oldest and most iconic, but Rothenburg ob der Tauber is where it genuinely feels like stepping inside a snow globe. I route clients through both plus a lesser-known local market that locals actually attend. Boutique hotels in the old towns book out fast."},{"i":"tf-seasonal__festival-02","t":"French Christmas Markets","c":"Seasonal & Festival","r":"Western Europe","s":"November \u2013 December","ss":{"spring":false,"summer":false,"autumn":false,"winter":true},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1543342384-1f1350e27861?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Strasbourg  \u00b7  Colmar  \u00b7  Paris  \u00b7  Lyon  \u00b7  Bordeaux","n":"Strasbourg is the capital of Christmas in France and deserves two full days. Colmar is smaller, quieter, and somehow even more beautiful, half-timbered houses strung with lights above canals. Pair these with a night in Paris lit for the season and you have a near-perfect winter week."},{"i":"tf-seasonal__festival-03","t":"Chinese New Year","c":"Seasonal & Festival","r":"East Asia","s":"January \u2013 February","ss":{"spring":false,"summer":false,"autumn":false,"winter":true},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1563245372-f21724e3856d?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Hong Kong  \u00b7  Taipei  \u00b7  Singapore  \u00b7  Chengdu  \u00b7  Kyoto","n":"Hong Kong's New Year parade and harbour fireworks are extraordinary but the city fills completely, book six months minimum. Singapore's Chinatown celebrations run two full weeks and are often overlooked. The Lantern Festival that closes the New Year period is the single most beautiful night of the calendar."},{"i":"tf-seasonal__festival-04","t":"Rio Carnival","c":"Seasonal & Festival","r":"South America","s":"February \u2013 March","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":false,"autumn":false,"winter":true},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1518639192441-8fce0a366e2e?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Rio de Janeiro  \u00b7  Salvador  \u00b7  Olinda  \u00b7  S\u00e3o Paulo","n":"Sambadrome tickets are the single most important booking, the Champions Parade on the final Saturday night is what everyone comes for and those boxes sell out a year in advance. I also recommend adding Salvador de Bahia for a Carnival experience that is wilder, more authentic, and utterly different from Rio."},{"i":"tf-seasonal__festival-05","t":"Japan Cherry Blossom","c":"Seasonal & Festival","r":"Japan","s":"Late March \u2013 April","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":false,"autumn":false,"winter":false},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1522383225653-ed111181a951?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Tokyo  \u00b7  Kyoto  \u00b7  Osaka  \u00b7  Nara  \u00b7  Hiroshima","n":"The bloom window is 7\u201310 days at each location and shifts slightly north as spring progresses, which means a well-timed itinerary can chase the blossom from Kyushu to Tokyo over two weeks. I track the Japan Meteorological Corporation's forecasts and build flexibility into every sakura itinerary. Book accommodation a year out. No exceptions."},{"i":"tf-seasonal__festival-06","t":"Oktoberfest Bavaria","c":"Seasonal & Festival","r":"Bavaria","s":"Late September \u2013 October","ss":{"spring":false,"summer":false,"autumn":true,"winter":false},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1567696153798-9111f9cd3d0d?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Munich  \u00b7  Theresienwiese  \u00b7  Bavarian Alps  \u00b7  Salzburg","n":"The major beer tents require advance table reservations, walking in without one means standing. I handle tent bookings, hotel rooms within walking distance of the Wiesn, and I always add two days in the Bavarian Alps after the festival. The contrast between the chaos of Oktoberfest and the silence of Berchtesgaden is extraordinary."},{"i":"tf-seasonal__festival-07","t":"Diwali India","c":"Seasonal & Festival","r":"India","s":"October \u2013 November","ss":{"spring":false,"summer":false,"autumn":true,"winter":true},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1605714578656-00a82f41b2b4?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Jaipur  \u00b7  Varanasi  \u00b7  Udaipur  \u00b7  Mumbai  \u00b7  Amritsar","n":"Varanasi on Diwali night is one of the most spiritually powerful experiences I know of anywhere in travel, ten thousand diyas floating on the Ganges. Jaipur's Amber Fort illuminated and Udaipur's lake palaces reflected in light are equally extraordinary. The key is routing between them so you don't miss any of the main night."},{"i":"tf-seasonal__festival-08","t":"Mardi Gras New Orleans","c":"Seasonal & Festival","r":"New Orleans","s":"February \u2013 March","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":false,"autumn":false,"winter":true},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1569949381669-ecf31ae8e613?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"French Quarter  \u00b7  Garden District  \u00b7  Magazine Street  \u00b7  Trem\u00e9","n":"The Bacchus and Endymion parades the weekend before Fat Tuesday are the biggest and most spectacular. Bourbon Street is the obvious choice, but the Uptown parade route along St. Charles Avenue is where locals actually watch. I book a balcony or grandstand position well in advance so you have a real vantage point without fighting the crowd."},{"i":"tf-sports__active-01","t":"Scottish Golf Pilgrimage","c":"Sports & Active","r":"Scotland","s":"May \u2013 October","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":false,"autumn":true,"winter":false},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1587174486073-ae5e5cff23aa?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"St Andrews  \u00b7  Turnberry  \u00b7  Royal Troon  \u00b7  Carnoustie  \u00b7  Muirfield","n":"The Old Course ballot at St Andrews is the most coveted tee time in golf, I navigate the application process and have relationships with private members who can secure access. Turnberry's Ailsa Course with the lighthouse in view is the most visually dramatic round of golf on earth. I pair every golf trip with a whisky distillery evening, the two belong together."},{"i":"tf-sports__active-02","t":"Pebble Beach California Golf","c":"Sports & Active","r":"California","s":"Year-Round","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":true,"autumn":true,"winter":true},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1535131749006-b7f58c99034b?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Pebble Beach  \u00b7  Cypress Point  \u00b7  Spyglass Hill  \u00b7  Monterey Peninsula","n":"Cypress Point is one of the most exclusive golf clubs in the world, access requires member sponsorship and I have those relationships. Pebble Beach tee times and lodge rooms at the same time need to be booked simultaneously; they're linked and both go fast. I always extend into Big Sur and, for the right client, add a Napa wine country finish."},{"i":"tf-sports__active-03","t":"The Masters Augusta","c":"Sports & Active","r":"Augusta, Georgia","s":"April","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":false,"autumn":false,"winter":false},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1593111774240-d529f12cf4bb?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Augusta National  \u00b7  Amen Corner  \u00b7  Savannah  \u00b7  Charleston","n":"Tournament badges at Augusta National are among the most difficult tickets in sport, held within families for generations. I work through legitimate secondary market connections to source them and I am always honest about what's possible. Practice round tickets are more accessible and the atmosphere is extraordinary. Either way, the experience is like nothing else in American sport."},{"i":"tf-sports__active-04","t":"Formula 1 Grand Prix Circuit","c":"Sports & Active","r":"Global Circuit","s":"March \u2013 November","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":false,"autumn":false,"winter":true},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1598136490941-30d885318abd?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Monaco  \u00b7  Monza  \u00b7  Silverstone  \u00b7  Spa  \u00b7  Singapore  \u00b7  Suzuka","n":"Monaco is the only Grand Prix where being in the principality during race week is the experience, the circuit runs through the streets so there's nowhere bad to be. Paddock Club hospitality is the standard for serious F1 travel. Monza and Spa both have extraordinary race-day atmospheres and great surrounding regions to build a full trip around."},{"i":"tf-sports__active-05","t":"Alps Ski Season","c":"Sports & Active","r":"European Alps","s":"December \u2013 April","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":false,"autumn":false,"winter":true},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1548777123-e216912df7d8?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Verbier  \u00b7  Zermatt  \u00b7  Courchevel  \u00b7  Val d'Is\u00e8re  \u00b7  Cortina","n":"Verbier and Zermatt are the twin peaks of alpine skiing, Verbier for the off-piste and the social scene, Zermatt for the Matterhorn backdrop and the most dramatic mountain landscape in the Alps. Courchevel 1850 is where you go for the chalet experience at its most refined. I book ski-in chalets with private chefs and instructors, the full version of this trip."},{"i":"tf-sports__active-06","t":"Ski Japan Hokkaido Powder","c":"Sports & Active","r":"Hokkaido, Japan","s":"January \u2013 March","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":false,"autumn":false,"winter":true},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1551524164-687a55dd1126?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Niseko  \u00b7  Rusutsu  \u00b7  Furano  \u00b7  Kiroro  \u00b7  Sapporo","n":"Hokkaido receives more snow than anywhere else on earth that has a functioning ski resort, sometimes fifteen meters in a single season. The champagne powder here is a different material entirely from anything in the Alps. I always pair Niseko with a few days in Sapporo and at least one night in a traditional onsen ryokan. The cultural component makes it a completely different ski trip."},{"i":"tf-sports__active-07","t":"Tour de France Experience","c":"Sports & Active","r":"France","s":"July","ss":{"spring":false,"summer":true,"autumn":false,"winter":false},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1541625602330-2277a4c46182?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Paris  \u00b7  Alpe d'Huez  \u00b7  Col du Galibier  \u00b7  Pyrenees  \u00b7  Champs-\u00c9lys\u00e9es","n":"Alpe d'Huez is the most famous climb in cycling, the road is painted with nations' flags and the crowd is twenty deep for five kilometres of hairpin. The Champs-\u00c9lys\u00e9es final stage is the most beautiful finish in sport. I build itineraries that position you at multiple stages so you see the race at very different speeds and scales."},{"i":"tf-sports__active-08","t":"Liveaboard Scuba Diving","c":"Sports & Active","r":"Global Oceans","s":"Year-Round","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":true,"autumn":true,"winter":true},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1682687982501-1e58ab814714?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Red Sea  \u00b7  Maldives  \u00b7  Raja Ampat  \u00b7  Palau  \u00b7  Cocos Island","n":"Raja Ampat in Indonesian Papua has been called the most biodiverse marine environment on earth, the colour and density of life on the reef is something photographs genuinely cannot convey. The Red Sea is the best value liveaboard diving in the world. Palau's Blue Corner is the greatest drift dive on the planet. The vessel you choose matters enormously and I know which operators run the best boats."},{"i":"tf-sports__active-09","t":"Camino de Santiago","c":"Sports & Active","r":"Spain","s":"April \u2013 October","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":false,"autumn":true,"winter":false},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1599059813005-6a7e7b72bb6e?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Saint-Jean-Pied-de-Port  \u00b7  Pamplona  \u00b7  Burgos  \u00b7  Le\u00f3n  \u00b7  Santiago","n":"The Camino Franc\u00e9s from Saint-Jean-Pied-de-Port is the classic, 800 kilometres, roughly 35 days at a walking pace. I work with clients on the version that suits them: full Camino, last 100km from Sarria, or the Portuguese Way for quieter roads. Private accommodation along the route can be booked in advance and makes an enormous difference to the experience."},{"i":"tf-sports__active-10","t":"Safari on Horseback","c":"Sports & Active","r":"Kenya & Botswana","s":"June \u2013 October","ss":{"spring":false,"summer":true,"autumn":true,"winter":false},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1557804506-669a67965ba0?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Masai Mara  \u00b7  Laikipia Plateau  \u00b7  Okavango Delta  \u00b7  Lewa Downs","n":"Horseback safari is the most intimate form of wildlife encounter there is, animals don't register horses as a threat the way they do vehicles, which means you approach at distances no Land Cruiser ever achieves. The Laikipia Plateau in Kenya with Offbeat Safaris is the gold standard. Botswana's Okavango by horseback with Abu Camp is a different experience entirely but equally extraordinary. Riding"},{"i":"tf-sports__active-11","t":"Surf Escapes World Class Breaks","c":"Sports & Active","r":"Global","s":"Year-Round","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":true,"autumn":true,"winter":true},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1505118380757-91f5f5632de0?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Uluwatu, Bali  \u00b7  Ericeira, Portugal  \u00b7  North Shore, Oahu  \u00b7  Jeffreys Bay","n":"Ericeira in Portugal is Europe's only World Surfing Reserve, incredible waves for intermediate to advanced surfers, charming town, great food, and far less crowded than the Algarve. Bali's Uluwatu is the dream wave for experienced surfers. The North Shore in November through February for the Eddie and the Pipe Masters is the greatest surf spectacle on earth even if you're only watching from the sa"},{"i":"tf-food__wine-01","t":"Italy Culinary Deep Dive","c":"Food & Wine","r":"Northern Italy","s":"Spring & Autumn","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":false,"autumn":true,"winter":false},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1498579150354-977475b7ea0b?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Bologna  \u00b7  Emilia-Romagna  \u00b7  Modena  \u00b7  Parma  \u00b7  Tuscany","n":"Bologna is the best food city in Italy, possibly in the world, and it is almost entirely overlooked by Americans. The Emilia-Romagna region produces Parmigiano-Reggiano, prosciutto di Parma, balsamic from Modena, and the best fresh pasta on earth. I build itineraries that go inside the production of each. Osteria Francescana in Modena requires a reservation made months in advance."},{"i":"tf-food__wine-02","t":"France Wine & Gastronomy","c":"Food & Wine","r":"France","s":"September \u2013 October","ss":{"spring":false,"summer":false,"autumn":true,"winter":false},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1559329255-b5c5b4b12cc2?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Burgundy  \u00b7  Lyon  \u00b7  Bordeaux  \u00b7  Champagne  \u00b7  Rh\u00f4ne","n":"Burgundy in harvest is the most atmospheric place in wine country anywhere in the world, the vendange fills every village with activity, the vines turn gold and red, and the cellars open for the season. Lyon has more Michelin stars per capita than any other city in France and the traditional bouchons serve one of the world's great lunches for twenty euros. I build a trip that earns its Michelin di"},{"i":"tf-food__wine-03","t":"Spain Pintxos & Rioja Trail","c":"Food & Wine","r":"Northern Spain","s":"Spring & Autumn","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":false,"autumn":true,"winter":false},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1546069901-ba9599a7e63c?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"San Sebasti\u00e1n  \u00b7  Rioja  \u00b7  Bilbao  \u00b7  Navarra  \u00b7  Basque Country","n":"San Sebasti\u00e1n's Parte Vieja has more Michelin stars per square metre than anywhere on earth, and the pintxos bars in the old town serve food of equal complexity for three euros a piece. Arzak and Mugaritz require advance reservations. The Rioja harvest in late September is one of the great wine travel experiences: bodegas open, the landscape turns gold, and the atmosphere is extraordinary."},{"i":"tf-food__wine-04","t":"Japan Sake, Ramen & Omakase","c":"Food & Wine","r":"Japan","s":"Year-Round","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":true,"autumn":true,"winter":true},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1569050467447-ce54b3bbc37d?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Tokyo  \u00b7  Osaka  \u00b7  Kyoto  \u00b7  Kanazawa  \u00b7  Hiroshima","n":"Tokyo has more Michelin stars than Paris, and some of the greatest meals are at twelve-seat counter restaurants that cost as much as a flight. I navigate the reservation system, which operates partly in Japanese and requires local assistance. Kanazawa on the Sea of Japan coast has what many consider the finest seafood market in the country and almost no international visitors."},{"i":"tf-food__wine-05","t":"Peru Lima's World-Class Food","c":"Food & Wine","r":"South America","s":"Year-Round","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":true,"autumn":true,"winter":true},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1504674900247-0877df9cc836?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Lima  \u00b7  Miraflores  \u00b7  Barranco  \u00b7  Sacred Valley  \u00b7  Amazon","n":"Central by Virgilio Mart\u00ednez has held a top-five position on the World's 50 Best Restaurants list for years. The tasting menu is a vertical journey through Peru's altitude zones, from the deep Amazon to the high Andes, using ingredients most people have never heard of. Reservations require booking months in advance and I handle all of it. The broader Lima food scene is extraordinary even without C"},{"i":"tf-food__wine-06","t":"Southeast Asia Street Food Circuit","c":"Food & Wine","r":"Southeast Asia","s":"November \u2013 April","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":false,"autumn":false,"winter":true},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1555396273-367ea4eb4db5?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Bangkok  \u00b7  Penang  \u00b7  Singapore  \u00b7  H\u1ed9i An  \u00b7  Hanoi","n":"Penang is the street food capital of Southeast Asia, possibly of the world, and most Americans have never been. Georgetown's hawker centres serve some of the most complex, satisfying food anywhere for two or three dollars a plate. I pair it with Bangkok for the energy and range, Singapore for the organised perfection of its hawker culture, and H\u1ed9i An for the most beautiful setting in which anyone"},{"i":"tf-food__wine-07","t":"Whisky Distillery Trail Scotland","c":"Food & Wine","r":"Scotland","s":"May \u2013 October","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":false,"autumn":true,"winter":false},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1527281400683-1aae777175f8?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Speyside  \u00b7  Islay  \u00b7  Highland  \u00b7  Campbeltown  \u00b7  Orkney","n":"Islay is the island that produces the world's most distinctive whisky and it is extraordinary to visit, eight distilleries on an island twenty-five miles long, each with a completely different character. The annual F\u00e8is \u00ccle festival in late May opens casks and warehouses that are normally closed to the public. Speyside has over fifty distilleries in a valley the size of a county. I build the route"},{"i":"tf-food__wine-08","t":"Champagne & Cheese","c":"Food & Wine","r":"Northern France","s":"Year-Round","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":true,"autumn":true,"winter":true},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1510812431401-41d2bd2722f3?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Reims  \u00b7  \u00c9pernay  \u00b7  Normandy  \u00b7  Paris  \u00b7  Loire Valley","n":"The chalk cellars under Reims hold tens of millions of bottles and are among the most atmospheric spaces in French food culture. Krug and Bollinger offer private cellar tours with older vintages that don't appear anywhere publicly. In Normandy, the combination of Camembert, Calvados, and fresh seafood at a seaside table is one of the unsung great meals of France. I pair the two regions into one of"},{"i":"tf-wellness__retreat-01","t":"Bali Wellness & Yoga Retreat","c":"Wellness & Retreat","r":"Bali, Indonesia","s":"Year-Round","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":true,"autumn":true,"winter":true},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1544161515-4ab6ce6db874?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Ubud  \u00b7  Sidemen  \u00b7  Munduk  \u00b7  Tegallalang  \u00b7  Seminyak","n":"The wellness infrastructure in Ubud is genuinely extraordinary, world-class teachers, serious retreat programmes, and the Balinese spiritual context gives it a dimension that Tulum or Sedona simply can't replicate. I match clients to the right retreat based on what they actually need: rigorous and transformative, or gentle and restorative. The difference matters enormously."},{"i":"tf-wellness__retreat-02","t":"Maldives Digital Detox & Spa","c":"Wellness & Retreat","r":"Indian Ocean","s":"November \u2013 April","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":false,"autumn":false,"winter":true},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1573843981267-be1999ff37cd?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"North Mal\u00e9 Atoll  \u00b7  Baa Atoll  \u00b7  Addu Atoll  \u00b7  Rasdhoo","n":"Several Maldives resorts now offer formal digital detox programmes, devices locked away on arrival, no screens in villas, the day structured entirely around water, movement, and meals. Six Senses Laamu and Soneva Fushi both do this exceptionally well. The effect of three days without a phone in an environment this beautiful is genuinely difficult to overstate."},{"i":"tf-wellness__retreat-03","t":"Japanese Onsen Ryokan Circuit","c":"Wellness & Retreat","r":"Japan","s":"October \u2013 April","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":false,"autumn":true,"winter":false},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1542051841857-5f90071e7989?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Hakone  \u00b7  Kinosaki  \u00b7  Beppu  \u00b7  Nyuto Onsen  \u00b7  Kusatsu","n":"Nyuto Onsen in Akita Prefecture in the snow is one of the most beautiful and serene experiences in all of Japan travel, remote mountain ryokans, outdoor baths in deep snow, complete silence except for the forest. Kinosaki Onsen in Hyogo is the classic tanyu, seven public baths, everyone walking the town in yukata. I build circuits that move between the iconic and the deeply hidden."},{"i":"tf-wellness__retreat-04","t":"Ayurveda Kerala India","c":"Wellness & Retreat","r":"Kerala, India","s":"October \u2013 March","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":false,"autumn":true,"winter":false},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1602515521450-7c1d3f7f8c67?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Varkala  \u00b7  Kovalam  \u00b7  Alleppey Backwaters  \u00b7  Munnar  \u00b7  Kochi","n":"Kerala is the home of authentic Ayurveda, not the watered-down spa version but the full therapeutic tradition practised by vaidyas whose knowledge has passed through generations. A proper Panchakarma programme requires a minimum of two weeks and a genuine commitment. The results clients describe are consistently remarkable. I pair it with backwater houseboat days and Munnar tea country so the trip"},{"i":"tf-wellness__retreat-05","t":"Swiss Alps Wellness","c":"Wellness & Retreat","r":"Switzerland","s":"Winter & Summer","ss":{"spring":false,"summer":true,"autumn":false,"winter":true},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1506905925346-21bda4d32df4?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Leukerbad  \u00b7  Vals  \u00b7  Gstaad  \u00b7  Davos  \u00b7  St. Moritz","n":"Therme Vals by Peter Zumthor is the most architecturally extraordinary spa in the world, a building entirely hewn from local quartzite with thermal pools at different temperatures in spaces that feel ancient and futuristic simultaneously. Access is deliberately limited. The B\u00fcrgenstock Resort above Lake Lucerne has one of the finest cliff-edge spa facilities in Europe. I build Swiss wellness trips"},{"i":"tf-wellness__retreat-06","t":"Morocco Hammam & Desert Silence","c":"Wellness & Retreat","r":"Morocco","s":"October \u2013 April","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":false,"autumn":true,"winter":false},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1489749798305-4fea3ae63d43?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Marrakech  \u00b7  Merzouga  \u00b7  Sahara  \u00b7  Atlas Mountains  \u00b7  Agafay","n":"Morocco's wellness proposition is unique, it moves between the intense sensory richness of the medina and the absolute silence of the Sahara. La Mamounia's hammam is one of the great spa experiences in the world. The desert at Merzouga, with no light pollution and silence so complete you can hear your own heartbeat, is one of the most powerful restorative environments I know. I plan the transition"},{"i":"tf-seasonal__festival-09","t":"Running of the Bulls","c":"Seasonal & Festival","r":"Northern Spain","s":"July 6\u201314","ss":{"spring":false,"summer":true,"autumn":false,"winter":false},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1558618047-3c8c76ca7d13?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Pamplona  \u00b7  San Ferm\u00edn  \u00b7  Basque Country  \u00b7  Navarra","n":"San Ferm\u00edn is not just the encierro. It is nine days of the most exuberant street festival in Europe, with the best food in Spain in the surrounding region. Pamplona's hotels book out a year in advance at festival rates. I secure the right encierro viewing position on the route so clients see the run properly rather than catching a glimpse through a crowd. The Basque pintxos circuit in San Sebasti"},{"i":"tf-seasonal__festival-10","t":"Songkran Water Festival","c":"Seasonal & Festival","r":"Thailand","s":"April 13\u201315","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":false,"autumn":false,"winter":false},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1578662996442-48f60103fc96?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Chiang Mai  \u00b7  Bangkok  \u00b7  Sukhothai  \u00b7  Chiang Rai","n":"Chiang Mai is the epicentre of Songkran and the most extraordinary place in Thailand to experience it. The moat around the old city becomes a continuous water fight for three days, interspersed with the genuinely moving temple ceremonies and Buddha bathing rituals that are the actual heart of the festival. Bangkok does Songkran at a larger scale but Chiang Mai does it better. I combine both with t"},{"i":"tf-seasonal__festival-11","t":"Burning Man","c":"Seasonal & Festival","r":"Nevada","s":"Late August \u2013 Labor Day","ss":{"spring":false,"summer":true,"autumn":false,"winter":false},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1504253492562-b1ed9e13ba99?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Black Rock Desert  \u00b7  Black Rock City  \u00b7  The Playa  \u00b7  Nevada","n":"Burning Man is unlike anything else I plan and requires a completely different kind of preparation. Tickets come through a lottery that opens months before the event and the main sale sells out in minutes. I navigate the ticket process, connect clients with established theme camps for community and infrastructure, and handle all the pre-event logistics including gear, transport from Reno, and the"},{"i":"tf-seasonal__festival-12","t":"Edinburgh Festival Fringe","c":"Seasonal & Festival","r":"Scotland","s":"August","ss":{"spring":false,"summer":true,"autumn":false,"winter":false},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1535378620166-273708d44e4c?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Edinburgh  \u00b7  Royal Mile  \u00b7  The Meadows  \u00b7  Scottish Highlands","n":"The Edinburgh Fringe is the largest arts festival in the world and the city transforms entirely. Every pub basement, church hall, and converted space becomes a venue. I work with a local Fringe expert to curate a show schedule that goes beyond the obvious headliners and finds the genuinely extraordinary smaller productions. I pair the Fringe with the Royal Military Tattoo at the Castle and add a H"},{"i":"tf-seasonal__festival-13","t":"Venice Carnival","c":"Seasonal & Festival","r":"Italy","s":"February","ss":{"spring":false,"summer":false,"autumn":false,"winter":true},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1514890547357-a9ee288728e0?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Venice  \u00b7  Piazza San Marco  \u00b7  Grand Canal  \u00b7  Palazzi Privati","n":"The public Carnival in Piazza San Marco is extraordinary but the private masked balls in the historic palazzi are where Venice Carnival truly lives. I secure invitations to the Casino Palazzo and Il Ballo del Doge, the two most celebrated private balls, which require advance booking and formal Venetian costume. I also arrange for a local mask atelier to costume clients properly. Venice in winter f"},{"i":"tf-seasonal__festival-14","t":"Coachella & Festival Circuit","c":"Seasonal & Festival","r":"California","s":"April","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":false,"autumn":false,"winter":false},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1493676304819-0d7a8d026dcf?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Indio  \u00b7  Palm Springs  \u00b7  Los Angeles  \u00b7  Joshua Tree","n":"Coachella done right is completely different from Coachella done wrong. General admission in the heat with no shade or plan is genuinely unpleasant. VIP passes with a proper Palm Springs base, a private shuttle to the grounds, and a curated set schedule is an extraordinary weekend. I book the Ace Hotel or a Palm Springs mid-century estate rental, arrange the transport, and add Joshua Tree and the"},{"i":"tf-sports__active-12","t":"Rugby World Cup","c":"Sports & Active","r":"Global","s":"Every 4 Years","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":true,"autumn":true,"winter":true},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1508098682722-e99c43a406b2?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Host Nation  \u00b7  Pool Stages  \u00b7  Quarter-Finals  \u00b7  Final","n":"The Rugby World Cup is the third largest sporting event in the world and the atmosphere rivals the FIFA World Cup with a fraction of the logistical chaos. Past hosts have included France, Japan, England, New Zealand, and Australia. I plan the trip around a combination of pool stage matches plus a knockout round, building the host nation touring itinerary around the fixture schedule. Japan 2019 was"},{"i":"tf-food__wine-09","t":"Bourbon Trail Kentucky","c":"Food & Wine","r":"Kentucky","s":"Year-Round","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":true,"autumn":true,"winter":true},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1602435399853-cd4e3ceaa2c2?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Louisville  \u00b7  Bardstown  \u00b7  Lexington  \u00b7  Loretto  \u00b7  Lawrenceburg","n":"95% of the world's bourbon is made within a short drive of Louisville and the distillery culture here is as developed and serious as Scotland's whisky trail. The difference is that Americans rarely think to treat it as a travel destination. Buffalo Trace, Pappy Van Winkle's home distillery, offers private tours that require advance booking and personal connection. I pair the distillery circuit wit"},{"i":"tf-sports__active-13","t":"Sailing Private Charter","c":"Sports & Active","r":"Global","s":"Year-Round","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":true,"autumn":true,"winter":true},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1567899378494-47b22a2ae96a?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Greek Islands  \u00b7  BVI  \u00b7  Croatia  \u00b7  French Polynesia  \u00b7  Norway","n":"A private sailing charter fundamentally changes how you experience a coastline. You go where no ferry serves and anchor where no hotel exists. The Greek Cyclades in May or September on a crewed gulet gives couples and small groups access to bays that see twenty boats a season rather than twenty thousand. The BVI in January through April has the most reliable trade winds in the Caribbean and the Vi"},{"i":"tf-honeymoon__romance-01","t":"Amalfi Coast Honeymoon","c":"Honeymoon & Romance","r":"Honeymoon & Romance","s":"Italy","ss":{"spring":false,"summer":false,"autumn":false,"winter":false},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1533587851505-d119e13fa0d7?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Positano  \u00b7  Ravello  \u00b7  Capri  \u00b7  Sorrento  \u00b7  Private Villa","n":"The Amalfi Coast is arguably the most beautiful coastline in the world and it delivers on that promise when planned correctly. I book cliff-face terraces in Positano where breakfast arrives as the boats below are just starting their engines. Ravello's Villa Rufolo garden overlooking the sea at dusk is where I send couples for their first evening. Private boat hire for the week so you move on your"},{"i":"tf-honeymoon__romance-02","t":"Bali Private Villa Romance","c":"Honeymoon & Romance","r":"Honeymoon & Romance","s":"Indonesia","ss":{"spring":false,"summer":false,"autumn":false,"winter":false},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1555400038-63f5ba517a47?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Ubud  \u00b7  Uluwatu  \u00b7  Seminyak  \u00b7  Nusa Penida  \u00b7  Sidemen","n":"Bali's private villa scene is extraordinary for honeymooners. I book properties where your own pool looks over rice paddies and a private chef arrives each morning. I structure the itinerary so Ubud comes first for the cultural and spiritual depth, then the coast for the final stretch. The Balinese blessing ceremony I arrange for couples on their second day is something people consistently describ"},{"i":"tf-honeymoon__romance-03","t":"Maldives Overwater Honeymoon","c":"Honeymoon & Romance","r":"Honeymoon & Romance","s":"Indian Ocean","ss":{"spring":false,"summer":false,"autumn":false,"winter":false},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1510414842594-a61c69b5ae57?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"North Mal\u00e9  \u00b7  Baa Atoll  \u00b7  Ari Atoll  \u00b7  Private Island Resorts","n":"The Maldives is the honeymoon destination people dream about and then book incorrectly. Resort selection is everything here and the quality range is enormous. I match couples to the right atoll and property based on their actual priorities. I also arrange the private sandbank dinner, bioluminescence night swim, and underwater breakfast that transform a good trip into an unforgettable one."},{"i":"tf-honeymoon__romance-04","t":"Tuscany Wine Country Romance","c":"Honeymoon & Romance","r":"Honeymoon & Romance","s":"Italy","ss":{"spring":false,"summer":false,"autumn":false,"winter":false},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1476103130780-9c3e6e5a5b46?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Chianti  \u00b7  Montalcino  \u00b7  San Gimignano  \u00b7  Val d'Orcia  \u00b7  Siena","n":"I book vineyard estates in Tuscany where the couple wakes up in the middle of a working Chianti property, walks through the vines before breakfast, and has a private cellar tasting each evening before dinner. The Val d'Orcia in September after the harvest is the most photographically perfect landscape in Italy and entirely worth timing a honeymoon around."},{"i":"tf-honeymoon__romance-05","t":"Paris Anniversary","c":"Honeymoon & Romance","r":"Honeymoon & Romance","s":"France","ss":{"spring":false,"summer":false,"autumn":false,"winter":false},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1431274172761-fca41d930114?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Le Marais  \u00b7  Saint-Germain  \u00b7  Montmartre  \u00b7  Loire Valley  \u00b7  Champagne","n":"Paris for an anniversary requires a different itinerary than Paris for a first visit. I skip the tourist circuit entirely and build around the best hotel in the right arrondissement, a three-Michelin-star dinner secured months in advance, a private museum morning before the doors open, and a day in the Loire Valley ch\u00e2teau country. The Champagne cellars at \u00c9pernay make a perfect two-night extensio"},{"i":"tf-honeymoon__romance-06","t":"Santorini Couples Escape","c":"Honeymoon & Romance","r":"Honeymoon & Romance","s":"Greece","ss":{"spring":false,"summer":false,"autumn":false,"winter":false},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1570077188670-e3a8d69ac5ff?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Oia  \u00b7  Fira  \u00b7  Caldera Views  \u00b7  Private Yacht  \u00b7  Ammoudi Bay","n":"Santorini's cave hotels are among the most architecturally unique romantic accommodations in the world. I avoid July and August and book May or September for couples so they have the island at a manageable pace. Private yacht for two days so you escape the village crowds and access the island from the water. The caldera sunset from Oia is genuinely as extraordinary as photographed."},{"i":"tf-honeymoon__romance-07","t":"Safari Honeymoon","c":"Honeymoon & Romance","r":"Honeymoon & Romance","s":"East Africa","ss":{"spring":false,"summer":false,"autumn":false,"winter":false},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1612392062798-b3f50df6de4d?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Serengeti  \u00b7  Ngorongoro  \u00b7  Zanzibar  \u00b7  Masai Mara  \u00b7  Lamu Island","n":"A safari honeymoon is consistently the most memorable trip I plan for couples. The combination of a private tented camp in the Serengeti followed by a week in Zanzibar or Lamu is essentially perfect: extraordinary wildlife and total solitude in the bush, then complete surrender on a white sand coast. I use only camps with private outdoor bathtubs and butler service and the payoff is significant."},{"i":"tf-family__multi-gen-01","t":"European Family Summer","c":"Family & Multi-Gen","r":"Family & Multi-Gen","s":"Europe","ss":{"spring":false,"summer":false,"autumn":false,"winter":false},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1467003909585-2f8a72700288?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Italy  \u00b7  France  \u00b7  England  \u00b7  Spain  \u00b7  Switzerland","n":"European family summers work best when anchored in one or two private villa bases rather than moving every night. I typically combine a Tuscan villa week where the whole family can spread out with a Paris or London city segment. Kids remember the pizza-making class in Florence and the Harry Potter studio tour outside London for decades. I plan so the adults get what they came for too."},{"i":"tf-family__multi-gen-02","t":"Costa Rica Family Adventure","c":"Family & Multi-Gen","r":"Family & Multi-Gen","s":"Central America","ss":{"spring":false,"summer":false,"autumn":false,"winter":false},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1596402184320-417e7178b2cd?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Arenal  \u00b7  Monteverde  \u00b7  Manuel Antonio  \u00b7  Tortuguero  \u00b7  Osa Peninsula","n":"Costa Rica is one of the best family adventure destinations in the Western Hemisphere. Children remember the sloth hanging above the breakfast terrace and the zip line through the cloud forest for years. I plan it so the days have enough activity for the kids and enough beauty and quiet for the adults. Tortuguero for sea turtle nesting is one of the most extraordinary natural experiences a family"},{"i":"tf-family__multi-gen-03","t":"Japan Family Cultural Trip","c":"Family & Multi-Gen","r":"Family & Multi-Gen","s":"Japan","ss":{"spring":false,"summer":false,"autumn":false,"winter":false},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1545569341-9eb8b30979d9?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Tokyo  \u00b7  Kyoto  \u00b7  Nara  \u00b7  Hiroshima  \u00b7  Osaka","n":"Japan is one of the best family destinations in the world for children old enough to engage with it. The shinkansen alone is worth the trip for most kids. Nara's deer park is universally beloved at every age. I navigate the logistics so Japan feels effortless. The food is the best gateway: ramen workshops, conveyor belt sushi, and Osaka street food keep every age engaged all day."},{"i":"tf-family__multi-gen-04","t":"Caribbean Family Beach","c":"Family & Multi-Gen","r":"Family & Multi-Gen","s":"Caribbean","ss":{"spring":false,"summer":false,"autumn":false,"winter":false},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1506905925346-21bda4d32df4?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Turks & Caicos  \u00b7  St. Lucia  \u00b7  Antigua  \u00b7  Anguilla  \u00b7  Barbados","n":"Turks and Caicos is the top family beach destination in the Caribbean. Grace Bay is one of the best beaches in the world and the water is calm and waist-deep for a hundred metres. For multi-gen trips where grandparents are included, I look at private villa rentals in Barbados or Antigua where the whole group can be together with a cook and pool and everyone has their own pace."},{"i":"tf-family__multi-gen-05","t":"African Safari Family","c":"Family & Multi-Gen","r":"Family & Multi-Gen","s":"Africa","ss":{"spring":false,"summer":false,"autumn":false,"winter":false},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1516426122078-c23e76319801?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"South Africa  \u00b7  Kenya  \u00b7  Tanzania  \u00b7  Botswana  \u00b7  Rwanda","n":"South Africa is the best entry-point safari for families with young children because the Big Five are accessible and the infrastructure is excellent. Kenya and Tanzania are better for older children who can handle longer drives and more remote conditions. I match the destination to the ages of the children. A safari is genuinely one of the most transformative experiences a child can have and I pla"},{"i":"tf-family__multi-gen-06","t":"Disney & Orlando Done Right","c":"Family & Multi-Gen","r":"Family & Multi-Gen","s":"Florida","ss":{"spring":false,"summer":false,"autumn":false,"winter":false},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1520250497591-112f2f40a3f4?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Walt Disney World  \u00b7  Universal  \u00b7  Kennedy Space Center  \u00b7  Florida Keys","n":"Disney is one of the most logistically complex domestic trips there is and most families do it inefficiently. I know the park opening strategies, the Lightning Lane booking windows, the dining reservations that open 60 days out, and the resort that puts you closest to where you need to be each morning. Done correctly, the experience is genuinely extraordinary. Done incorrectly, it is exhausting an"},{"i":"tf-family__multi-gen-07","t":"Gal\u00e1pagos Family Expedition","c":"Family & Multi-Gen","r":"Family & Multi-Gen","s":"Pacific","ss":{"spring":false,"summer":false,"autumn":false,"winter":false},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1544551763-92a4e8e7c7e0?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Santa Cruz  \u00b7  Isabela  \u00b7  San Crist\u00f3bal  \u00b7  Espa\u00f1ola  \u00b7  Ecuador","n":"The Gal\u00e1pagos is one of the most extraordinary family destinations in the world for children old enough to appreciate it. The animals have no fear of humans. A sea lion will swim circles around your child in the water. A blue-footed booby will stand its ground as you step around it on the path. I book family-focused expedition vessels with excellent naturalist guides who engage children directly."},{"i":"tf-river_cruises__sailing-01","t":"Danube River Cruise","c":"River Cruises & Sailing","r":"Central Europe","s":"Spring & Autumn","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":false,"autumn":true,"winter":false},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1549887534-1541e9326b9e?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Vienna  \u00b7  Budapest  \u00b7  Bratislava  \u00b7  Linz  \u00b7  Melk  \u00b7  Passau","n":"The Danube is the most elegant river cruise route in Europe. Vienna and Budapest bookend it perfectly. The Wachau Valley between Melk and Krems has castle ruins, apricot orchards, and Gr\u00fcner Veltliner vineyards on the banks. I book smaller ships that fit the medieval locks and dock in village centres rather than industrial ports on the edge of town."},{"i":"tf-river_cruises__sailing-02","t":"Rhine & Moselle River Cruise","c":"River Cruises & Sailing","r":"Western Europe","s":"Spring & Autumn","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":false,"autumn":true,"winter":false},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1541262476577-9fdf0b8a2c12?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Amsterdam  \u00b7  Cologne  \u00b7  Rhine Gorge  \u00b7  Moselle Valley  \u00b7  Strasbourg  \u00b7  Basel","n":"The Rhine Gorge between Koblenz and Bingen has a castle or ruin on every hillside and is one of the most dramatic river passages in Europe. Adding the Moselle tributary puts you in the heart of German Riesling country: steep slate vineyards above the river and wine estates that have been in the same family for generations. The Amsterdam embarkation days deserve two nights minimum."},{"i":"tf-river_cruises__sailing-03","t":"Douro Valley Wine Cruise","c":"River Cruises & Sailing","r":"Portugal","s":"Spring & Autumn","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":false,"autumn":true,"winter":false},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1504150558240-0b4fd8946624?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Porto  \u00b7  R\u00e9gua  \u00b7  Pinh\u00e3o  \u00b7  Barca d'Alva  \u00b7  Salamanca","n":"The Douro is the most beautiful river valley in Europe and the least known by American travelers. The terraced vineyards above Pinh\u00e3o in September at harvest are extraordinary. Port wine quintas that have been making wine for 300 years open their cellars for river cruise passengers. Porto deserves three nights before embarkation. The Salamanca Spain extension over the border is exceptional."},{"i":"tf-river_cruises__sailing-04","t":"Mekong River","c":"River Cruises & Sailing","r":"Southeast Asia","s":"November \u2013 March","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":false,"autumn":false,"winter":true},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1583417319070-4a69db38a482?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Ho Chi Minh City  \u00b7  Mekong Delta  \u00b7  Phnom Penh  \u00b7  Siem Reap  \u00b7  Angkor Wat","n":"The Mekong combines two of the most extraordinary countries in Southeast Asia in a single itinerary. I book small boutique vessels rather than large ships and I always add two nights in Siem Reap so clients see Angkor correctly rather than rushing it as a shore excursion. Phnom Penh is essential and often skipped. I always include it with appropriate preparation for the Killing Fields visit."},{"i":"tf-river_cruises__sailing-05","t":"Amazon River Expedition","c":"River Cruises & Sailing","r":"South America","s":"Year-Round","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":true,"autumn":true,"winter":true},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1576506542790-51244b486a6b?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Manaus  \u00b7  Meeting of the Waters  \u00b7  Rio Negro  \u00b7  Peruvian Amazon  \u00b7  Iquitos","n":"The Amazon at low water season exposes river beaches and concentrated wildlife that the high water season covers. Pink river dolphins, caimans, sloths, and macaw clay licks accessible by small skiff from a floating lodge. I use small expedition vessels with naturalist guides rather than large cruise ships. The Peruvian Amazon from Iquitos is more pristine than the Brazilian side and I recommend it"},{"i":"tf-river_cruises__sailing-06","t":"Nile River Egypt","c":"River Cruises & Sailing","r":"Egypt","s":"October \u2013 April","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":false,"autumn":true,"winter":false},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1568322503739-3c95f06fca7d?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Luxor  \u00b7  Valley of the Kings  \u00b7  Esna  \u00b7  Edfu  \u00b7  Kom Ombo  \u00b7  Aswan","n":"A Nile cruise between Luxor and Aswan is one of the oldest and most extraordinary travel itineraries in the world. I use small traditional dahabiyas or boutique cruise ships rather than the large floating hotels that crowd the locks. The temples at Karnak, the Valley of the Kings, Edfu, and Abu Simbel seen in sequence from the water give a sense of ancient Egypt that no museum ever conveys."},{"i":"tf-river_cruises__sailing-07","t":"Norwegian Fjords Sailing","c":"River Cruises & Sailing","r":"Norway","s":"June \u2013 August","ss":{"spring":false,"summer":true,"autumn":false,"winter":false},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1520769945061-0a448c463865?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Bergen  \u00b7  Hardangerfjord  \u00b7  Sognefjord  \u00b7  Geirangerfjord  \u00b7  Lofoten","n":"Sailing the Norwegian fjords on a private or chartered yacht gives you access to anchorages no cruise ship can reach. The N\u00e6r\u00f8yfjord is so narrow at points that the cliffs seem close enough to touch from either rail. The midnight sun means you can sail until eleven at night and the light never fails. I book fully crewed charter yachts for this and the experience is extraordinary."},{"i":"tf-river_cruises__sailing-08","t":"Greek Islands Sailing Flotilla","c":"River Cruises & Sailing","r":"Greece","s":"May \u2013 October","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":false,"autumn":true,"winter":false},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1548516173-3cabfa4607e9?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Athens  \u00b7  Hydra  \u00b7  Cyclades  \u00b7  Dodecanese  \u00b7  Ionian Islands","n":"Sailing the Greek islands gives you access to bays and coves that no ferry route serves. I book fully crewed gulets or sailing yachts depending on the group and route. The Dodecanese: Rhodes, Symi, Patmos. The Cyclades: Santorini, Folegandros, Sifnos. The Ionian for gentler winds and greener islands. I plan the route based on the season and the client's sailing experience."},{"i":"tf-river_cruises__sailing-09","t":"BVI Caribbean Sailing Charter","c":"River Cruises & Sailing","r":"British Virgin Islands","s":"November \u2013 May","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":false,"autumn":false,"winter":true},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1505459668311-8dfac7952bf0?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Tortola  \u00b7  Virgin Gorda  \u00b7  Jost Van Dyke  \u00b7  Anegada  \u00b7  The Baths","n":"The BVI are the best sailing destination in the Caribbean for consistent trade winds, short passages between islands, protected anchorages, and extraordinary snorkeling. The Baths at Virgin Gorda are genuinely spectacular. Anegada's reef is one of the best dive sites in the Caribbean and the lobster dinner on the beach at sunset is not optional. I book crewed catamarans for groups and bareboat cha"},{"i":"tf-unesco__history-01","t":"Egypt Pyramids & the Valley","c":"UNESCO & History","r":"North Africa","s":"October \u2013 April","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":false,"autumn":true,"winter":false},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1539650116574-75c0c6d73f6e?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Cairo  \u00b7  Giza  \u00b7  Luxor  \u00b7  Valley of the Kings  \u00b7  Aswan  \u00b7  Abu Simbel","n":"Egypt requires a specialist Egyptologist guide rather than a generic tour leader. The difference between visiting the Valley of the Kings with someone who reads the hieroglyphics and knows the history of every tomb versus someone who herds you from site to site is the difference between a transformative experience and a very hot walk past old rocks. I secure credentialed guides and early morning a"},{"i":"tf-unesco__history-02","t":"Greece The Ancient World","c":"UNESCO & History","r":"Greece","s":"April \u2013 June, September \u2013 October","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":true,"autumn":true,"winter":false},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1603565816030-6b389eeb23cb?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Athens  \u00b7  Delphi  \u00b7  Olympia  \u00b7  Mycenae  \u00b7  Epidaurus  \u00b7  Thessaloniki","n":"Most people visit the Acropolis mid-morning in the heat with three thousand other tourists. I book the first entry slot when the gates open, before the tour groups and before the Mediterranean sun makes the marble blinding. Delphi is consistently underrated and the setting on a Parnassus mountainside above the plain is extraordinary. Epidaurus in summer when the ancient theatre still hosts perform"},{"i":"tf-unesco__history-03","t":"Cambodia Angkor & the Khmer","c":"UNESCO & History","r":"Southeast Asia","s":"November \u2013 March","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":false,"autumn":false,"winter":true},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1538099130682-4ded7ca7f0ea?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Siem Reap  \u00b7  Angkor Wat  \u00b7  Angkor Thom  \u00b7  Ta Prohm  \u00b7  Phnom Penh","n":"Angkor Wat at sunrise is one of the genuine bucket-list experiences in world travel. The reflection in the moat as the towers go from silhouette to gold is worth the flight alone. I secure the dawn entry permits and position clients at the reflecting pool before anyone else is there. Three full days in the Angkor complex minimum. Phnom Penh is essential and often skipped \u2014 I always include it with"},{"i":"tf-unesco__history-04","t":"Peru Inca Trail Deep Dive","c":"UNESCO & History","r":"South America","s":"May \u2013 September","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":false,"autumn":true,"winter":false},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1526392060635-9d6019884377?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Cusco  \u00b7  Sacred Valley  \u00b7  Machu Picchu  \u00b7  Ollantaytambo  \u00b7  Lake Titicaca","n":"Machu Picchu timed entry tickets sell out months in advance and must be secured early. Altitude acclimatization in Cusco is non-negotiable and I build it into every itinerary. Beyond the headline site, the Sacred Valley is staggering: Ollantaytambo is one of the most impressive Inca fortresses in existence and almost no one lingers long enough. Lake Titicaca and the floating reed islands of the Ur"},{"i":"tf-unesco__history-05","t":"Italy Rome & Pompeii","c":"UNESCO & History","r":"Italy","s":"April \u2013 June, September \u2013 October","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":true,"autumn":true,"winter":false},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1552832230-c0197dd311b5?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Rome  \u00b7  the Vatican  \u00b7  Pompeii  \u00b7  Herculaneum  \u00b7  Paestum  \u00b7  Naples","n":"The Colosseum floor and underground hypogeum require skip-the-line access booked weeks ahead. The Vatican Museums and Sistine Chapel visited before public opening hours \u2014 when Michelangelo's ceiling is the only sound in the room \u2014 is one of the great private access experiences I arrange in Europe. Herculaneum is better preserved than Pompeii and has a fraction of the crowds. I always send clients"},{"i":"tf-unesco__history-06","t":"China Great Wall & Beyond","c":"UNESCO & History","r":"China","s":"April \u2013 June, September \u2013 October","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":true,"autumn":true,"winter":false},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1508804185872-d7badad00f7d?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Beijing  \u00b7  Great Wall  \u00b7  Forbidden City  \u00b7  Xi'an  \u00b7  Terracotta Army  \u00b7  Shanghai","n":"The Great Wall at Mutianyu or Jinshanling at dawn, before the day visitors arrive, with mist in the valleys and no one else on the battlements, is one of the great travel experiences in the world. The Terracotta Army in Xi'an is more vast and more strange than any photograph conveys. I always include a hutong neighbourhood walk in Beijing and a morning at the Temple of Heaven as a counterweight to"},{"i":"tf-unesco__history-07","t":"Jordan Petra & the Decapolis","c":"UNESCO & History","r":"Middle East","s":"March \u2013 May, October","ss":{"spring":true,"summer":false,"autumn":true,"winter":false},"g":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1548248823-ce16a73b6d49?w=900&q=85&auto=format&fit=crop","tl":"Petra  \u00b7  Jerash  \u00b7  Wadi Rum  \u00b7  Amman  \u00b7  Madaba  \u00b7  Dead Sea","n":"Petra at dawn, before the tourist crowds arrive, is one of the most genuinely moving experiences in all of travel. The Siq narrows and then opens and the Treasury is there and it stops you. Jerash is one of the best-preserved Roman provincial cities in the world and almost nobody goes. I pair them in a single itinerary that also includes a Wadi Rum night under the stars and a Dead Sea morning for"}]
